<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24/1089a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-10T17:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1941—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>757. Mr. Hopkins has asked the Department to forward to you as
                                further reply to your 1896, December 4, the following text of a
                                letter from the President to Stettinius, Lend-Lease Administrator:
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“For purposes of implementing the authority conferred upon
                                        you as Lend-Lease Administrator by Executive Order No. 8926,
                                        dated October 28, 1941 and in order to enable you to arrange
                                        for Lend-Lease aid to all nations already receiving aid in
                                        such manner as I shall have directed, whether directly or by
                                        way of retransfer, I hereby find that the defense of the
                                        following countries is vital to the defense of the United
                                        States: <list>
                                            <label>1.</label>
                                            <item>India, Burma, the Dominions of Australia, Canada,
                                                New Zealand and South Africa, (including mandated
                                                territories under Dominion mandate), Newfoundland,
                                                Southern Rhodesia and the British colonial
                                                dependencies (including mandated territories under
                                                British mandate).</item>
                                            <label>2.</label>
                                            <item>The Kingdom of Yugoslavia.</item>
                                            <label>3.</label>
                                            <item>The Kingdom of Egypt.”</item>
                                        </list></p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>